{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\n**Retire the band-aids** now that the ref-lock (C3) is proven, flip the default backend to `ref`,\nand remove the dead file-lock machinery + `merge=ours` entry, with a migration for existing repos.\n\n**Depends on: 2711-21bf-ab71-4136 (C3).** The ref backend must be wired and validated first;\nremoving the file backend / retry loop before C3 would leave the reconciler with no working lock.\n\n- Flip `[reconciler] lock_backend` default to `ref` and remove the `file` backend path from\n  `_advisory_lock.py` once the ref backend has baked.\n- **Remove the `b859-8fa1` retry loop** in `acquire_pass_lock` AND its now-dead helpers\n  (`_resolve_retry_budget`, `_LOCK_RETRY_BUDGET_DEFAULT`, `_compute_backoff_seconds`, and the\n  b859-only backoff constants). Retire the config key `lock_max_retries` (`_config_schema.py`\n  `ReconcilerConfig` field + coercion entry) and its env aliases\n  (`REBAR_RECONCILER_LOCK_MAX_RETRIES` + deprecated alias `REBAR_RECONCILER_LOCK_RETRY_BUDGET` in\n  `config.py`). Delete/adjust the tests that exercise them:\n  `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/state/test_advisory_lock_retry_jitter.py`, and the retry-budget\n  assertions in `tests/.../test_config_file_wiring.py` + `test_ev3c_env_renames.py`.\n- **Deprecation path for the retired config key.** `lock_max_retries` removal is operator-visible;\n  rather than a hard break, treat a still-present `lock_max_retries` as **deprecated** — emit a\n  one-time deprecation warning (config-load path) and ignore it — and note the removal in\n  `docs/config.md` + the changelog, so existing operator configs do not error on upgrade.\n- **Remove `.reconciler-*` from `_GITATTRIBUTES`** in `src/rebar/_commands/init.py` (leave\n  `.bridge_state/* merge=ours` untouched — that is WS-1 binding data, out of scope), and update\n  `tests/interfaces/store/test_gitattributes_merge.py` to assert `.reconciler-*` is absent and\n  `.bridge_state/*` still present.\n- **Migration for already-initialized trackers:** `_commit_gitattributes` is create-if-absent only,\n  so editing the constant does not fix existing repos. Add an update-migration arm (mirroring the\n  `_commit_gitignore` line-migration) that strips the `.reconciler-* merge=ours` line from an\n  already-committed `.gitattributes`. Idempotent; on git failure, log-and-continue (do not abort).\n- **One-time cleanup:** remove any pre-existing `.reconciler-pass-lock`/`.reconciler-phase-gate`\n  committed on the tickets branch from the old scheme (a single named helper, idempotent, invoked\n  from exactly one site — reconciler startup; state the site explicitly).\n- Extend the ref-lock ADR to record that the b859 loop is superseded by the C3 self-healing lock.\n\n## Design decisions (resolves plan-review ambiguities; binding on the implementation)\n\n1. **Precise removal set (verified dead by grep, not by line number).** After the file backend is\n   gone, delete every symbol left with zero consumers: the file dispatch branches in\n   `acquire_pass_lock` / `release_pass_lock` / `check_phase_gate`; `_write_file_to_tickets_branch`,\n   `_delete_file_from_tickets_branch`, `_commit_in_detached_tickets_worktree`,\n   `_git_show_tickets_file`, the file-based `check_pass_lock`, the `_LOCK_FILE`/`_GATE_FILE`\n   constants; the b859 outer-retry loop + `_resolve_retry_budget` / `_LOCK_RETRY_BUDGET_DEFAULT` /\n   `_compute_backoff_seconds`; and `_cas_advance_with_retry` / `_cas_backoff_seconds` /\n   `_jittered_backoff` / the backoff constants **iff** grep confirms no remaining consumer once the\n   file backend is deleted. **KEEP** `_cas_once` and `_is_cas_mismatch` — they are imported by\n   `_ref_lock.py` and are the shared CAS discriminator. Every deletion is justified by a\n   zero-consumer grep across `src/` and `tests/`.\n2. **`lock_backend` post-removal.** Keep the key (default now `ref`); the acquire/release/gate\n   dispatch becomes unconditional ref. A still-configured `lock_backend=file` is\n   **deprecated-and-ignored**: a one-time warning is logged and the ref backend is used anyway\n   (rollback via `file` is intentionally gone — ref is proven). The `{file, ref}` choice validator\n   stays so the value still parses.\n3. **`lock_max_retries` deprecation mechanics.** Removing the `ReconcilerConfig.lock_max_retries`\n   field means a config that still sets it hits `Config.from_mapping`'s existing **unknown-key\n   path**, which WARNs-and-ignores under the default non-strict load — exactly the required\n   \"one-time warning, not a load error\". Verify no reconciler config-load site passes `strict=True`\n   (which would reject it); if one does, add `lock_max_retries` to an explicit deprecated-and-ignored\n   set rather than letting it error. The env aliases are removed from `config.py`'s env map.\n4. **Migrations — two distinct, idempotent, single-site helpers.**\n   (a) *gitattributes line-strip* lives in `init.py` (an update arm on `_commit_gitattributes`,\n   mirroring the `_commit_gitignore` line-migration): if the committed `.gitattributes` contains a\n   `.reconciler-*` line, rewrite without it and commit; on any git failure log-and-continue (never\n   abort init). (b) *committed-lock-file cleanup* is a single named helper (e.g.\n   `_purge_committed_reconciler_locks`) invoked from exactly one site — the reconciler startup in\n   `rebar_reconciler/__main__.py:main()`, before the pass acquires — that deletes any\n   `.reconciler-pass-lock` / `.reconciler-phase-gate` still committed on the tickets branch (no-op if\n   absent → idempotent; git failure log-and-continue).\n5. **Regression test.** A test asserts no `.reconciler-*` path is ever committed to the tickets\n   branch after a ref-backend pass (and that the cleanup helper removes a pre-seeded one).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `lock_backend` defaults to `ref`; the file-lock backend + the `b859` retry loop are deleted,\n      along with `_resolve_retry_budget`, `_LOCK_RETRY_BUDGET_DEFAULT`, `_compute_backoff_seconds`,\n      any then-dead backoff/CAS-retry helpers (grep-verified), the `lock_max_retries` config field +\n      coercion + env aliases, and their tests. `_cas_once`/`_is_cas_mismatch` are kept (used by\n      `_ref_lock`). A configured `lock_backend=file` is deprecated-and-ignored (one-time warning).\n- [ ] `.reconciler-*` is removed from `_GITATTRIBUTES`; `.bridge_state/*` is left in place;\n      `tests/interfaces/store/test_gitattributes_merge.py` updated accordingly.\n- [ ] A `.gitattributes` update-migration (mirroring `_commit_gitignore`) strips\n      `.reconciler-* merge=ours` from already-committed trackers; idempotent; git failure logs and\n      continues rather than aborting.\n- [ ] A single, named, idempotent startup migration (invoked from `__main__.main()` before acquire)\n      removes any pre-existing committed `.reconciler-*` files; a regression test asserts no\n      `.reconciler-*` path is ever committed to the tickets branch.\n- [ ] `lock_max_retries` is handled as deprecated-and-ignored (one-time warning, not a load error)\n      and its removal is documented in `docs/config.md` + changelog.\n- [ ] Full non-integration suite green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783234872905984001,"uuid":"00a073aa-5c0f-46e4-9cad-319ab0b2bc95"}